---
import ToolShell from '../../components/ToolShell.astro';
import ToolResultActions from '../../components/ToolResultActions.astro';

const groups = [
  { key: 'acquire', title: 'Acquire', questions: ['Our acquisition targets are calculated from product margin and customer value.', 'We know which campaigns or partners bring genuinely new customers.', 'We have a repeatable pipeline for ad creative, feed or organic-search improvement.'] },
  { key: 'convert', title: 'Convert', questions: ['We can identify the biggest points of friction in the product and checkout journey.', 'Store changes are prioritised from evidence rather than internal preference.', 'We can implement and measure commercial improvements without excessive delay.'] },
  { key: 'retain', title: 'Retain', questions: ['We know our repeat-purchase rate and time to second order by customer cohort.', 'Lifecycle journeys cover more than welcome and abandoned cart.', 'Email and retention activity is measured against incremental customer value.'] },
  { key: 'measure', title: 'Measure', questions: ['Critical ecommerce events and consent behaviour have been validated recently.', 'Store, analytics and channel reports use shared definitions for revenue and customers.', 'Weekly reporting makes the next decision clear rather than adding more metrics.'] },
];
---
<ToolShell title="Store growth assessment" metaTitle="Free Ecommerce Store Growth Assessment" eyebrow="Growth diagnostic" description="Score the commercial foundations across acquisition, conversion, retention and measurement, then get an immediate priority and practical next steps.">
  <div slot="hero-card" class="hero-score"><span>Four connected stages</span><div><b>A</b><b>C</b><b>R</b><b>M</b></div><p>The lowest score is not automatically the biggest project. It is the first constraint worth investigating.</p></div>
  <div slot="tool" class="tool-card assessment-card"><div class="assessment-intro"><span>12 statements · about 3 minutes</span><h2>How true is each statement today?</h2><p>Choose the answer that reflects the operating reality, not the process you intend to have.</p></div><form id="growth-assessment" class="assessment-form">{groups.map((group,groupIndex)=><fieldset data-group={group.key}><legend><span>0{groupIndex+1}</span><strong>{group.title}</strong></legend>{group.questions.map((question,index)=><div class="question"><p>{question}</p><div class="answer-row"><label><input type="radio" name={`${group.key}-${index}`} value="0" required /><span>Not true</span></label><label><input type="radio" name={`${group.key}-${index}`} value="1" /><span>Partly true</span></label><label><input type="radio" name={`${group.key}-${index}`} value="2" /><span>Consistently true</span></label></div></div>)}</fieldset>)}<button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Show my current constraint</button></form>
    <div class="result-panel" id="assessment-results" aria-live="polite"><div class="assessment-result-head"><div><span>Likely current constraint</span><h2 id="constraint-name">—</h2></div><div class="total-score"><strong id="total-score">—</strong><span>overall readiness</span></div></div><div class="score-bars" id="score-bars"></div><div class="recommendations"><h3>Investigate these next</h3><ol id="recommendations"></ol></div><div class="assessment-action"><div><strong>Use this as a starting hypothesis.</strong><p>The commercial impact and effort still need validation against your store data.</p></div><a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-arrow">Get a tailored review</a></div><ToolResultActions toolName="growth_assessment" resultId="assessment-results" resultTitle="Store growth assessment result" /></div>
  </div>
  <h2>What the four stages mean</h2><p><strong>Acquire</strong> covers the cost and quality of demand. <strong>Convert</strong> covers the store experience between landing and purchase. <strong>Retain</strong> covers the value created after the first order. <strong>Measure</strong> covers the reliability of the evidence used across all three.</p>
  <h2>Why the lowest score is only a hypothesis</h2><p>A weak measurement score can make every other stage look better or worse than it is. A weak conversion score may be more valuable to fix than launching another acquisition channel. Prioritisation should combine the score with financial impact, customer evidence and implementation effort.</p>
  <h2>A sensible next step</h2><ol><li>Validate the lowest-scoring statements with data or customer evidence.</li><li>Estimate the upside of fixing that constraint.</li><li>Identify dependencies that must be solved first.</li><li>Choose the smallest change that can create a reliable learning.</li></ol>
</ToolShell>
<script>
  const assessment=document.getElementById('growth-assessment');
  const recommendations={
    acquire:['Calculate break-even CAC and ROAS from contribution margin.','Separate new-customer performance from blended platform revenue.','Create a 90-day feed, creative or search-demand testing backlog.'],
    convert:['Review product and checkout friction using behaviour and customer language.','Prioritise hypotheses by impact, confidence and implementation effort.','Define one conversion improvement that can be shipped and measured cleanly.'],
    retain:['Measure repeat purchase and time to second order by acquisition cohort.','Audit lifecycle coverage beyond welcome and abandonment.','Choose retention metrics that account for discount and attribution cost.'],
    measure:['Validate critical ecommerce events, consent and deduplication.','Create shared definitions for net revenue, new customers, CAC and MER.','Reduce weekly reporting to the changes that require a decision.']
  };
  assessment?.addEventListener('submit',event=>{
    event.preventDefault();
    const data=new FormData(assessment);const scores={acquire:0,convert:0,retain:0,measure:0};
    for(const [name,value] of data.entries()){const key=name.split('-')[0];if(key in scores)scores[key]+=Number(value)}
    const weakest=Object.entries(scores).sort((a,b)=>a[1]-b[1])[0][0];
    const labels={acquire:'Acquisition economics and operating rhythm',convert:'Store conversion and implementation',retain:'Customer retention and repeat value',measure:'Measurement and decision confidence'};
    const total=Object.values(scores).reduce((sum,value)=>sum+value,0);const pct=Math.round(total/24*100);
    document.getElementById('constraint-name').textContent=labels[weakest];document.getElementById('total-score').textContent=`${pct}%`;
    document.getElementById('score-bars').innerHTML=Object.entries(scores).map(([key,value])=>`<div><span><strong>${key[0].toUpperCase()+key.slice(1)}</strong><b>${Math.round(value/6*100)}%</b></span><i><em style="width:${value/6*100}%"></em></i></div>`).join('');
    document.getElementById('recommendations').innerHTML=recommendations[weakest].map(item=>`<li>${item}</li>`).join('');
    const scoreSummary=Object.entries(scores).map(([key,value])=>`${key[0].toUpperCase()+key.slice(1)} readiness: ${Math.round(value/6*100)}%`);
    const results=document.getElementById('assessment-results');results.dataset.resultSummary=['Spires Digital — store growth assessment',`Likely current constraint: ${labels[weakest]}`,`Overall readiness: ${pct}%`,...scoreSummary,'Investigate next:',...recommendations[weakest].map((item,index)=>`${index+1}. ${item}`),'This is a starting hypothesis; validate commercial impact and effort against store data.'].join('\n');results.classList.add('active');results.scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'});
    window.trackSpiresEvent?.('tool_complete',{tool_name:'growth_assessment',result_type:weakest});
  });
</script>
<style>
  .hero-score>span,.assessment-intro>span{color:#91eadb;font-size:.68rem;font-weight:800;text-transform:uppercase}.hero-score>div{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:.4rem;margin:1rem 0}.hero-score b{display:grid;height:46px;place-items:center;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.12);border-radius:10px;background:rgba(255,255,255,.08);color:white}.hero-score b:last-child{background:rgba(117,230,211,.15);color:#91eadb}.hero-score p{color:#cbd2df;font-size:.78rem}.assessment-intro{margin-bottom:1.5rem}.assessment-intro>span{color:var(--violet-dark)}.assessment-intro h2{margin:.3rem 0}.assessment-intro p{color:var(--slate)}.assessment-form{display:grid;gap:1.3rem}.assessment-form fieldset{border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:var(--radius-sm);background:var(--canvas);overflow:hidden}.assessment-form legend{display:flex;gap:.6rem;align-items:center;padding:1rem 1rem 0;color:var(--ink)}.assessment-form legend span{display:grid;width:30px;height:30px;place-items:center;border-radius:8px;background:var(--violet-soft);color:var(--violet-dark);font-size:.62rem}.question{padding:1rem}.question+.question{border-top:1px solid var(--line)}.question p{margin-bottom:.7rem;color:var(--ink);font-size:.86rem;font-weight:650}.answer-row{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:.45rem}.answer-row label{cursor:pointer}.answer-row input{position:absolute;opacity:0}.answer-row span{display:grid;min-height:42px;place-items:center;padding:.5rem;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:8px;background:white;color:var(--slate);font-size:.68rem;font-weight:700;text-align:center}.answer-row input:checked+span{border-color:var(--violet);background:var(--violet-soft);color:var(--violet-dark)}.answer-row input:focus-visible+span{outline:3px solid #8b87ff}.result-panel{background:#effbf8}.assessment-result-head{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;gap:1rem;align-items:center}.assessment-result-head>div>span{color:var(--success);font-size:.68rem;font-weight:800;text-transform:uppercase}.assessment-result-head h2{max-width:520px;margin-top:.3rem;font-size:1.6rem}.total-score{text-align:right}.total-score strong,.total-score span{display:block}.total-score strong{color:var(--success);font-size:2.3rem}.total-score span{color:var(--muted);font-size:.62rem}.score-bars{display:grid;gap:.7rem;margin:1.3rem 0}.score-bars>div{padding:.8rem;border-radius:9px;background:white}.score-bars span{display:flex;justify-content:space-between}.score-bars strong,.score-bars b{color:var(--ink);font-size:.72rem}.score-bars i{display:block;height:7px;margin-top:.5rem;overflow:hidden;border-radius:999px;background:#e7ebf0}.score-bars em{display:block;height:100%;border-radius:999px;background:var(--mint)}.recommendations{padding:1rem;border-radius:10px;background:white}.recommendations h3{font-size:1rem}.recommendations ol{display:grid;gap:.45rem;margin-top:.7rem;padding-left:1.2rem;color:var(--slate);font-size:.78rem}.assessment-action{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;gap:1rem;align-items:center;margin-top:1rem;padding:1rem;border-radius:10px;background:var(--ink);color:#cbd2df}.assessment-action strong{color:white}.assessment-action p{font-size:.7rem}.assessment-action .btn{flex:0 0 auto}@media(max-width:650px){.answer-row{grid-template-columns:1fr}.assessment-result-head,.assessment-action{align-items:stretch;flex-direction:column}.total-score{text-align:left}}
</style>
